If you want to manage rust-analyzer manually then this utility is for you.
Here, the "manually" means you do not use extensions live in VS Code or something similar to update rust-analyzer automatically.

**Remember to set RA_HOME in your shell profile.** This environment variable shows where rust-analyzer lives in.

USAGE:
    ra-updater [OPTIONS] [SUBCOMMAND]

OPTIONS:
    -a, --mirror     F** the [GFW](https://wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Firewall)
    -c, --check      Just to check if there is a available update
    -f, --force      Force to update rust-analyzer in current release channel
    -h, --help       Print help information
    -m, --mt         Download rust-analyzer in multi-threaded way
    -V, --version    Print version information

SUBCOMMANDS:
    channel    Set release channel for rust-analyzer
    help       Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

